{"build_type":"library","description":"Layer-2 eventfd-replacement, POST side (wake-object-eventfd-replacement-DESIGN section 3). Marks the doorbell ready and wakes any thread parked on it. `word` is the address of the doorbell's shared marker (e.g. g_work_futex_addr). Writes 1 (ready) into the marker, then calls the layer-1 release primitive to wake up to one parked waiter via FUTEX_WAKE. This is the [= eventfd write] role: a binary readiness signal, not a counter. Lost-wakeup safety comes from writing the marker BEFORE releasing (a waiter that has not yet parked sees the 1 on its fast-path re-check). Replaces the inline array_write+sys-202 doorbell wake in the scheduler doorbell loop.","module_name":"announce-readiness-waking-doorbell-waiters","package_name":"announce-readiness-waking-doorbell-waiters","function_definitions":{"announce-readiness-waking-doorbell-waiters":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"word","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"atomic_fetch_add","result_assignment_variable":"c","address":"word","delta":"one"},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"seq","base":"word","index":"two","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sinc","variable_type":"i64","assignment_opera